# Rust generator crate

## Error handling

Use `crate::error::Result<T>` and `GeneratorError`. Map I/O and XML errors via `From` impls; use `GeneratorError::Format` for domain errors.

```rust
// ❌ avoid in library code
let doc = DialectDocument::parse(path).unwrap();

// ✅
let doc = DialectDocument::parse(path)?;
```

## Module layout

- `src/xml/` — parsing only; no code generation
- `src/generate/<lang>/` — dialect rendering, runtime, examples per language
- `src/driver.rs` — orchestration shared by CLI and UI; keep serde types here
- Integration tests in `tests/generator.rs`, not `#[cfg(test)]` in lib unless unit-testing a private helper

## Traits

- `LanguageGenerator::render` — dialect file content from `DialectDocument`
- `LanguageRuntimeGenerator` — runtime files from `templates/<lang>/`
- `LanguageExampleGenerator` — example files from `templates/<lang>/examples/`

## After edits

```bash
cargo fmt
cargo check
cargo test
```

Add or update tests in `tests/generator.rs` when generation output changes. Assert on meaningful substrings (class names, CRC values, enum names).
